comments.body:
Good work, maybe add a link here?

https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/keras/applications/resnet/preprocess_input

If we are going to add the link here, it should be added to all other nets too, I think.
Additionally I noticed that densenet, nasnet are missing caution too (and reference is not as in https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/71964116c54e3f1ad9686b9fb4987d526a15d8a7).
I can convert this PR to update all other networks in the folder?

Revisiting this a few days later I remembered that this caution will actually generate proper link on TensorFlow site (see [here](https://www.tensorflow.org/api_docs/python/tf/keras/applications/ResNet101V2) for an example), so I'll mark this as resolved. Still need to update other nets with the same change though.
